---
import CircleCheckIcon from "./CircleCheckIcon.astro";
---

<section
    id="description"
    class="z-10
        w-full px-5 md:px-10 lg:px-20 py-10 md:py-20
        flex flex-col items-center justify-center place-content-center
        gap-10 lg:gap-20 max-w-7xl
        bg-indigo-50 dark:bg-indigo-950"
>
    <h2
        class="font-light leading-8 lg:leading-10 text-center
            text-xl lg:text-2xl xl:text-3xl max-w-3xl
            text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-400"
    >
        <span class="font-semibold text-sky-500">Awesome Command Line</span>
        is a free and open source project to empower everyone with the command line
        application available on all computers. The project will include a downloadable
        guide book and a video series that walk you through 21 essential commands
        chapter by chapter. The 6-week mini-series kicks off the project by familiarizing
        you with the fundamental command line concepts that are needed for building
        your next great idea, or for supercharging your daily computing workflow.
    </h2>
    <h1
        id="did-you-know"
        class="font-sans font-medium dark:font-normal
			leading-8 md:leading-10 lg:leading-14
			text-center
			text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl
			text-transparent bg-clip-text
        	bg-gradient-to-r from-indigo-600 dark:from-indigo-500
            from-20% to-fuchsia-800 dark:to-sky-300 to-90%
			z-0 w-full md:w-1/2"
    >
        Did You Know?
    </h1>
    <ul>
        <li
            class="flex flex-row gap-2 items-center
                italic text-light text-xl md:text-2xl mb-5"
        >
            <CircleCheckIcon styles="min-w-10 size-10 text-indigo-400" />
            <span>
                The <span class="text-sky-500 dark:text-sky-400"
                    >Internet
                </span>was built using the command line.
            </span>
        </li>
        <li
            class="flex flex-row gap-2 items-center
                italic text-light text-xl md:text-2xl mb-5"
        >
            <CircleCheckIcon styles="min-w-10 size-10 text-indigo-400" />
            <span>
                The <span class="text-sky-500 dark:text-sky-400"
                    >World Wide Web
                </span>was built using the command line.
            </span>
        </li>
        <li
            class="flex flex-row gap-2 items-center
                italic text-light text-xl md:text-2xl mb-5"
        >
            <CircleCheckIcon styles="min-w-10 size-10 text-indigo-400" />
            <span>
                <span class="text-sky-500 dark:text-sky-400">Bitcoin </span>was
                built using the command line.
            </span>
        </li>
        <li
            class="flex flex-row gap-2 items-center
                italic text-light text-xl md:text-2xl mb-5"
        >
            <CircleCheckIcon styles="min-w-10 size-10 text-indigo-400" />
            <span>
                The
                <span class="text-sky-500 dark:text-sky-400"
                    >Lightning Network
                </span>is being built using the command line.
            </span>
        </li>
        <li
            class="flex flex-row gap-2 items-center
                italic text-light text-xl md:text-2xl mb-5"
        >
            <CircleCheckIcon styles="min-w-10 size-10 text-indigo-400" />
            <span>
                If you can imagine it, <span
                    class="text-sky-500 dark:text-sky-400"
                    >you can build it.</span
                >
            </span>
        </li>
    </ul>
</section>
